  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women and Agroecology for Sustainable Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribute to the sustainable development of rural families, especially women, in communities within the area of influence of the high-altitude wetland Santurban, Colombia, by fostering agroecology as a strategy for adaptation to and mitigation of climate change, as well as for the protection of the ecosystem.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implementation of an agroecological school with learning-by-doing methodologies. Training and workshops to promote capacities for gender-transformative advocacy. Assembly of roofs for crop protection. Production of agroecological inputs for fertilisation and organic pest- and disease- control. Implementation of the Participatory Guarantee System. Commercialisation of surplus harvest in local circuits. Inventory of plant coverage, as well as native tree and shrub species, in each household. Implementation of native species seedbed. Planting of species to increase forest and plant cover. Construction of septic tanks.</narrative>
  </description>
